00:16:33,980 --> 00:16:35,510
what's your kind of dream,jenny?

258
00:16:35,750 --> 00:16:36,920
Gettin' out of this town.

259
00:16:36,930 --> 00:16:37,650
Goin' where?

260
00:16:37,660 --> 00:16:38,610
Anywhere.

261
00:16:38,620 --> 00:16:41,560
It's a nice place-  anywhere.I've been there myself many times.

262
00:16:41,570 --> 00:16:43,880
It's got to be better than secretarial school.

263
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:46,710
That so bad?

264
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:48,790
It's a train ride to squaresville.

265
00:16:49,580 --> 00:16:51,320
see,I wt to be a singer.

266
00:16:52,170 --> 00:16:54,020
Get in line. That's a hard dream.

267
00:16:54,030 --> 00:16:56,820
But it's mine.People in line aren't my problem.

268
00:16:56,830 --> 00:16:58,410
You sure are feisty,jenny.

269
00:16:58,460 --> 00:16:59,620
Born that way.

270
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:04,880
what the hell you doing with gramps?

271
00:17:04,890 --> 00:17:06,350
None of your business,skiz.

272
00:17:06,450 --> 00:17:07,180
We're going now.

273
00:17:07,190 --> 00:17:08,060
Get off of me!

274
00:17:08,070 --> 00:17:10,340
Why don't you take a walk? Cool off.

275
00:17:12,350 --> 00:17:15,200
Why don't you keep your nose out of it,old man,before I break it for you?

276
00:17:16,470 --> 00:17:18,550
Kid,you rode in here on a bicycle.

277
00:17:19,390 --> 00:17:21,000
I'm quaking in my boots.

278
00:17:24,560 --> 00:17:27,880
I'm staying,skiz,so scat.

279
00:17:28,050 --> 00:17:29,270
Woot de do.

280
00:17:42,630 --> 00:17:45,220
This skiz clown-- know his real name?

281
00:17:45,230 --> 00:17:46,740
Scott sienkovic.

282
00:17:47,190 --> 00:17:51,580
I remember because he made the front page of the papers a few months later.

283
00:17:51,590 --> 00:17:53,290
Boy scout of the year?

284
00:17:54,340 --> 00:17:55,890
Armed robbery.

285
00:17:56,420 --> 00:17:57,910
Shot a bank teller.

286
00:18:03,090 --> 00:18:05,810
Had it out for hawkins big time,skiz.

287
00:18:07,170 --> 00:18:08,800
And we know you're not shy with a firearm.

288
00:18:08,810 --> 00:18:11,680
Grown man going after a girl half his age.

289
00:18:11,950 --> 00:18:13,530
Guy deserved to get shot.

290
00:18:13,860 --> 00:18:16,090
You want to tell us where you were the night he died?

291
00:18:16,310 --> 00:18:21,370
Bowling at the thunderbird lanes.Me and 100 other kids heard that needle skip.

292
00:18:21,750 --> 00:18:23,300
we'll check that out,skiz.

293
00:18:23,310 --> 00:18:24,810
Woot de do.

294
00:18:25,460 --> 00:18:28,030
This jenny-- she your girlfriend long?

295
00:18:28,180 --> 00:18:31,680
Couple of months,before she got all obsessed with hawkins.

296
00:18:31,690 --> 00:18:32,650
How obsessed?

297
00:18:32,660 --> 00:18:34,460
She kept calling the radio,

298
00:18:34,470 --> 00:18:35,600
writing him letters,

299
00:18:35,610 --> 00:18:37,170
talking about him nonstop.

300
00:18:37,180 --> 00:18:38,830
You know,real psycho stuff.

301
00:18:38,840 --> 00:18:40,080
You think they had an affair?

302
00:18:40,090 --> 00:18:41,580
Must have.

303
00:18:41,590 --> 00:18:45,190
Why else would she give two pennies about that loser?

304
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:47,130
Sounds like it was a one-way street.

305
00:18:47,190 --> 00:18:49,910
She got crazier and crazier over it.

306
00:18:49,930 --> 00:18:53,270
One night we were in front of a real rock star,

307
00:18:53,280 --> 00:18:56,300
and as usual,all she cared about was the hawk.

308
00:18:58,380 --> 00:19:01,520
All right! Now here's the one you've been waiting for--

309
00:19:01,730 --> 00:19:04,550
little richard!

310
00:19:25,130 --> 00:19:26,770
skiz,you got to help me get to the hawk.

311
00:19:26,780 --> 00:19:27,900
Stop acting nutso,jenny.

312
00:19:27,910 --> 00:19:29,560
I got to see him. You don't understand!

313
00:19:29,570 --> 00:19:30,730
He's an old coot. Why do you care?

314
00:19:30,740 --> 00:19:32,730
Don't talk about him like that!

315
00:19:33,060 --> 00:19:35,170
You're on your own,dollface.

316
00:19:38,040 --> 00:19:40,530
do this,we'll go park later.

317
00:19:42,050 --> 00:19:42,930
Promise?

318
00:19:42,940 --> 00:19:44,840
You helping me get to him or not?

319
00:19:45,330 --> 00:19:46,220
Woot de do.

320
00:19:53,730 --> 00:19:55,020
We got to talk to the hawk.

321
00:19:55,510 --> 00:19:57,270
Yeah,and I got a date with jayne mansfield.

322
00:19:57,290 --> 00:19:58,070
You think you're funny?

323
00:19:58,080 --> 00:19:58,880
Hawk!

324
00:20:02,770 --> 00:20:05,150
hey! Why'd you stop taking my calls?

325
00:20:05,160 --> 00:20:06,130
I've been busy,jenny.

326
00:20:06,140 --> 00:20:07,740
You shouldn't even be back here,all right?

327
00:20:07,750 --> 00:20:09,230
I just...I just want to talk.

328
00:20:09,980 --> 00:20:11,160
About what?

329
00:20:11,170 --> 00:20:12,090
Us.

330
00:20:12,100 --> 00:20:13,150
Us?

331
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:15,800
Jenny,there is no us.

332
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:21,080
I made it for you.

333
00:20:27,170 --> 00:20:30,310
play it. You'll understand everything.

334
00:20:33,830 --> 00:20:35,450
I'll never forget you.

335
00:20:43,890 --> 00:20:45,070
"Scarlet rose."

336
00:20:45,520 --> 00:20:48,490
Same song hawk was playing on the radio when he was killed.

337
00:20:49,420 --> 00:20:51,000
Know where we can find this jenny?

338
00:20:51,020 --> 00:20:54,220
Ran into her after I got out of jail.

339
00:20:54,720 --> 00:20:57,240
All married.Mrs. Jenny monahan.

340
00:20:57,250 --> 00:20:59,750
Pretended like she didn't know me.

341
00:21:00,180 --> 00:21:01,680
That's a surprise.

342
00:21:02,990 --> 00:21:04,080
Can I get out of here?

343
00:21:04,090 --> 00:21:05,350
Yeah.

344
00:21:08,480 --> 00:21:10,710
Sounds like we got a groupie gone wild.

345
00:21:11,370 --> 00:21:14,240
At 17,you think your first love's your last.

346
00:21:14,280 --> 00:21:17,010
Yeah. Every fan knew where the hawk broadcast.

347
00:21:17,020 --> 00:21:18,810
I wonder if jenny found her way there.

348
00:21:18,820 --> 00:21:20,620
And found the hawk's gun.

349
00:21:34,870 --> 00:21:36,290
what's going on,mike?

350
00:21:36,840 --> 00:21:37,930
What do you mean?

351
00:21:39,220 --> 00:21:40,330
This.

352
00:21:42,360 --> 00:21:44,490
It's got to be be some kind of virus.

353
00:21:44,600 --> 00:21:46,070
Think I can afford to miss work?

354
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:47,650
The doc says you're okay physically.

355
00:21:47,660 --> 00:21:50,120
Oh,he's just pissed I'm late with his bills.

356
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:02,190
da called me again.

357
00:22:03,020 --> 00:22:05,410
Yeah,this coach fitzpatrick thing.

358
00:22:08,590 --> 00:22:11,920
The case is... falling apart.

359
00:22:13,600 --> 00:22:18,730
The only guy who agreed to testify is getting scared.

360
00:22:19,340 --> 00:22:21,650
He might go south on the stand.

361
00:22:24,120 --> 00:22:25,790
Judge could toss it.

362
00:22:29,730 --> 00:22:31,670
- You sure you don't remember anything?
- No way.

363
00:22:31,680 --> 00:22:33,300
I ask because...

364
00:22:34,840 --> 00:22:37,610
there was this one night you came home from practice.

365
00:22:37,620 --> 00:22:39,570
Oh,god,scotty,that was a long time ago.

366
00:22:39,580 --> 00:22:44,950
Yeah,but I remember,'cause... you were pretty messed up.

367
00:22:46,100 --> 00:22:47,900
You slept in your clothes.

368
00:22:55,870 --> 00:22:57,080
you okay,mike?

369
00:22:58,500 --> 00:22:59,720
I'm fine.

370
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:01,520
Go to sleep.

371
00:23:03,030 --> 00:23:05,020
Something happen at practice?

372
00:23:06,250 --> 00:23:07,450
No.

373
00:23:10,040 --> 00:23:11,450
Hey,why are you being so quiet?

374
00:23:11,460 --> 00:23:13,530
Just don't go there no more,okay?

375
00:23:13,830 --> 00:23:15,500
Don't go near the coach.

376
00:23:16,730 --> 00:23:17,950
Why?

377
00:23:23,340 --> 00:23:24,360
You want to play guess?

378
00:23:27,860 --> 00:23:29,260
Come on.

379
00:23:29,650 --> 00:23:30,950
Guess this song.

380
00:23:42,110 --> 00:23:43,510
you got it?

381
00:23:44,850 --> 00:23:48,010
Scotty,I'm too tired,okay?

382
00:23:49,710 --> 00:23:50,990
Okay.

383
00:23:51,370 --> 00:23:52,910
We'll play tomorrow night.

384
00:23:54,740 --> 00:23:56,590
All right. Night,mikey.

385
00:23:58,460 --> 00:23:59,190
Night.

386
00:24:16,020 --> 00:24:17,590
I don't remember that night.

387
00:24:19,030 --> 00:24:20,410
Well,what about that song?

388
00:24:21,200 --> 00:24:22,440
No.

389
00:24:23,370 --> 00:24:24,490
You're sure?

390
00:24:24,540 --> 00:24:25,480
I'm tired,scotty.

391
00:24:25,490 --> 00:24:28,740
That was the only time I ever saw you get so... bummed out.

392
00:24:28,750 --> 00:24:30,670
I mean,you were crying...

393
00:24:30,880 --> 00:24:34,750
if I was bawling,it was probably because that weasel jay shortz cheap-shotted me.

394
00:24:37,150 --> 00:24:40,340
Yeah. Probably.

395
00:24:40,480 --> 00:24:43,260
We'll talk later,all right? I'm just beat.

396
00:24:47,910 --> 00:24:49,080
Okay.

397
00:24:56,660 --> 00:24:59,540
you don't get better soon,I'm going to pound you.

398
00:24:59,550 --> 00:25:01,540
Oh,yeah,that'll be the day.

399
00:25:43,030 --> 00:25:43,960
How about a little music?

400
00:25:43,970 --> 00:25:45,200
May I?

401
00:26:30,890 --> 00:26:33,230
interesting lyrics you wrote for the hawk.

402
00:26:33,260 --> 00:26:34,690
How'd you get that record?

403
00:26:35,010 --> 00:26:37,020
Bones kept all of hawk's stuff,

404
00:26:37,460 --> 00:26:39,480
including the song he was playing when you killed him.

405
00:26:39,670 --> 00:26:42,130
Me? Oh,you're joking,right?

406
00:26:42,160 --> 00:26:44,840
Back then it was called a teenage crush.

407
00:26:44,850 --> 00:26:46,430
Now we call it stalking.

408
00:26:46,440 --> 00:26:49,830
I was a lonely,confused kid, not a murderer.

409
00:26:49,840 --> 00:26:51,740
Can't just take your word for it,jenny.

410
00:26:51,750 --> 00:26:54,240
I was at home that night with my sisters.

411
00:26:54,830 --> 00:26:59,060
Believe me,hawk had bigger problems than a lovesick teenybopper.

412
00:26:59,070 --> 00:27:00,730
What kind of problems we talking?

413
00:27:02,870 --> 00:27:07,870
One night... I snuck into the station to see him.

414
00:27:08,460 --> 00:27:10,420
I got an idea of what he was up against.

415
00:27:10,430 --> 00:27:11,210
Meaning what?

416
00:27:11,220 --> 00:27:13,150
The record companies.

417
00:27:13,410 --> 00:27:15,400
They were always trying to make him take payola.

418
00:27:15,410 --> 00:27:18,370
Hawk doesn't sound like the kind of dj that would take money to play a song.

419
00:27:18,380 --> 00:27:20,760
Well,that didn't stop them from trying.

420
00:27:28,640 --> 00:27:29,650
Thanks,ben.

421
00:27:30,120 --> 00:27:31,240
Didn't know you were buying dinner tonight.

422
00:27:31,250 --> 00:27:35,320
I sent you a record last week,expected it on the air by now.

423
00:27:36,420 --> 00:27:37,210
I'm not for sale.

424
00:27:37,220 --> 00:27:38,770
Everyone's for sale.

425
00:27:39,640 --> 00:27:41,610
Funny,I heard you play one of my groups today.

426
00:27:41,960 --> 00:27:43,680
Hey,I got nothing against your label.

427
00:27:43,690 --> 00:27:45,840
Was it that new warner mack tune? That's pretty hot.

428
00:27:45,920 --> 00:27:47,930
No,the darts,"square town."

429
00:27:47,940 --> 00:27:49,830
Oh,bones picked that one.

430
00:27:50,240 --> 00:27:51,680
I give him a pick each day.

431
00:27:51,690 --> 00:27:53,130
And he chose mine.

432
00:27:59,340 --> 00:28:01,500
are you saying that bones took money to play a song?

433
00:28:01,510 --> 00:28:03,810
Bones understands the game.

434
00:28:04,390 --> 00:28:06,270
Djs like you are dinosaurs.

435
00:28:06,510 --> 00:28:07,550
That right?

436
00:28:08,200 --> 00:28:10,240
We've got the money,the artists,the control.

437
00:28:10,250 --> 00:28:13,460
Radio is just my personal handshake to the buying public.

438
00:28:13,470 --> 00:28:15,090
And if the buying public doesn't want it?

439
00:28:15,100 --> 00:28:18,720
One choice of entree you eat, what's on the plate.

440
00:28:18,730 --> 00:28:21,780
You know what?People like you take everything that is real and good

441
00:28:21,790 --> 00:28:24,430
and you turn it into tinsel.

442
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:26,000
But the worst part...

443
00:28:26,460 --> 00:28:31,020
tinsel-man...  is that you don't even know it.

444
00:28:31,570 --> 00:28:34,100
Oh,so you're the big shot celebrity with all the answers,that it?

445
00:28:34,110 --> 00:28:35,800
No,I'm just like the kids.

446
00:28:35,810 --> 00:28:38,500
I'm a fan. I'm a damned fan of the music.

447
00:28:38,510 --> 00:28:42,130
Now,if you will excuse me,I have to sell some toothpaste.

448
00:28:42,140 --> 00:28:43,460
You give my best to bones.

449
00:28:44,050 --> 00:28:46,340
That's right! Zip toothpaste!

450
00:28:46,770 --> 00:28:48,550
If you want to keep your smile hip,

451
00:28:48,560 --> 00:28:50,640
you'd better brush with some zip!

452
00:28:59,270 --> 00:29:01,840
Gave up the singing career then and there.

453
00:29:01,850 --> 00:29:03,810
Saw how cutthroat it was.

454
00:29:04,020 --> 00:29:05,910
That the last time you saw the hawk?

455
00:29:06,740 --> 00:29:08,570
He looked crushed.

456
00:29:08,580 --> 00:29:10,660
So the hawk knew bones was on the take.

457
00:29:10,670 --> 00:29:13,430
And maybe hawk was going to do something about it.

458
00:29:16,700 --> 00:29:21,780
Your career is over if authorities knew you were taking payola,right,bones?

459
00:29:21,840 --> 00:29:25,820
Fcc was cracking down,lot of people's lives ruined over that.

460
00:29:26,730 --> 00:29:27,980
You can't prove I took money.

461
00:29:27,990 --> 00:29:29,590
We don't care about payola in '58.

462
00:29:29,600 --> 00:29:31,990
We care about who killed john hawkins.

463
00:29:32,400 --> 00:29:34,140
Hawk confront you on what you did?

464
00:29:34,240 --> 00:29:35,970
The same night he found out.

465
00:29:36,150 --> 00:29:37,310
Keep talking.

466
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:39,850
I never meant to betray him.

467
00:29:40,780 --> 00:29:42,280
But you did,bones.

468
00:29:42,910 --> 00:29:44,310
It didn't matter.

469
00:29:45,280 --> 00:29:47,550
Something had already changed in him.

470
00:29:50,620 --> 00:29:52,050
If I get my own show,

471
00:29:52,460 --> 00:29:54,880
you girls are my first guests.

472
00:30:01,540 --> 00:30:03,540
Bones,we got to talk.

473
00:30:03,550 --> 00:30:05,470
Hawk! Have a seat.

474
00:30:05,750 --> 00:30:10,770
This is,uh,this is gigi,and this is lulu.

475
00:30:10,990 --> 00:30:12,690
Gilugilu.

476
00:30:12,700 --> 00:30:13,940
You mind,girls?

477
00:30:14,700 --> 00:30:15,830
We need some privacy.

478
00:30:23,900 --> 00:30:24,790
hurry back.

479
00:30:26,830 --> 00:30:28,230
What are you doing here,bones?

480
00:30:28,290 --> 00:30:31,180
Mr. Ockley invited me.This is some shindig,huh?

481
00:30:31,190 --> 00:30:34,130
I got two chicks after me. Can you believe that?

482
00:30:34,140 --> 00:30:35,880
They're hookers,bones.

483
00:30:37,590 --> 00:30:38,860
Wh-what?

484
00:30:39,290 --> 00:30:42,690
No,lulu's A dance student, and gigi's A...

485
00:30:42,700 --> 00:30:43,660
stripper.

486
00:30:44,400 --> 00:30:46,300
I've seen her act,umbrellas.

487
00:30:48,140 --> 00:30:48,770
you're fooling.

488
00:30:48,780 --> 00:30:51,420
I know you took money to play that darts song.

489
00:30:55,460 --> 00:30:57,160
It was just one song.

490
00:30:57,170 --> 00:30:59,980
That one song means that they've got me over a barrel.

491
00:31:00,160 --> 00:31:01,060
I don't understand...

492
00:31:01,070 --> 00:31:02,790
I could go to jail...

493
00:31:05,080 --> 00:31:06,770
because of what you did.

494
00:31:07,090 --> 00:31:10,340
Mr. Ockley says it's how the game's played.

495
00:31:10,350 --> 00:31:12,480
You know what the game is,bones?

496
00:31:12,490 --> 00:31:16,190
It's the music and the fans who love it.

497
00:31:16,200 --> 00:31:18,270
And then there's all this.

498
00:31:18,280 --> 00:31:22,130
The dealmakers,the sellouts,the price of your soul.

499
00:31:23,140 --> 00:31:24,970
I'm sorry,hawk.

500
00:31:25,850 --> 00:31:27,410
I'm so sorry.

501
00:31:31,570 --> 00:31:33,070
What are you gonna do?

502
00:31:33,670 --> 00:31:35,120
I don't know,maybe leave philly for a while.

503
00:31:35,130 --> 00:31:36,030
What about your show?

504
00:31:36,040 --> 00:31:37,560
Aw,to hell with it.

505
00:31:38,190 --> 00:31:39,570
To hell with all of this.

506
00:31:40,360 --> 00:31:42,670
I got something more important in my life now.

507
00:31:43,890 --> 00:31:45,020
Jenny.

508
00:31:47,120 --> 00:31:48,320
but she's just a fan.

509
00:31:48,330 --> 00:31:49,770
No.

510
00:31:50,750 --> 00:31:52,430
She's more than that.

511
00:31:53,480 --> 00:31:55,920
Me and her gonna take a little trip out west.

512
00:31:58,000 --> 00:31:59,090
Hawk...

513
00:32:01,950 --> 00:32:03,880
I just wanted to be a winner.

514
00:32:05,400 --> 00:32:07,140
Like you.

515
00:32:07,520 --> 00:32:08,960
You always were,kid.

516
00:32:23,470 --> 00:32:25,340
Steep price. We all paid.

517
00:32:25,540 --> 00:32:27,150
Some more than others.

518
00:32:27,610 --> 00:32:30,480
So jenny and hawk were going away together?

519
00:32:30,490 --> 00:32:32,130
That was the plan.

520
00:32:33,660 --> 00:32:35,620
But,the next night, hawk was dead.

521
00:32:38,320 --> 00:32:41,190
Funny how jenny failed to mention her travel plans with hawk.

522
00:32:41,200 --> 00:32:42,780
Failed to mention a lot more than that.

523
00:32:43,110 --> 00:32:46,900
Follow me.That documentary dude? He's got nothing on me.

